race.comment: BASEMENT (4) was big odds last time but gave a huge sight after a fast early split, weakening late to finish a one length fifth (28.85) over 500m at this track. Has claims if he runs up to expectations. MCIVOR ALFY (6) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at this track over 660m behind Panama Rhode (39.05) in a Grade 4/5. Placed at his previous run. One of the main contenders. BRUTE FORCE (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (29.73) at Sandown behind Aston Rayner in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Must be included in calculations. BURN ALONG (8) did a good job to finish third last time out over 425m at this track (24.06) in a Special conditions H, the second top-three finish on the trot.
